title: Chinese Government donates drugs worth RMB 4.34 million to Myanmar Ministry of Health in April 2020 (Linked to Project ID#90263, #93378)
description: On April 8, 2020, the Chinese Government officially sent 12 medical experts from Yunnan Province medical institutions to Myanmar to help fight the spread of COVID-19 (see Project ID#93378). During their stay, the team visited 43 medical institutions in Rangoon and Mandalay and held more than 50 exchange activities. For example, they visited Mandalay General Hospital's Department of Emergency Medicine to observe COVID-19 patients and discussed best practices for treating them. The team returned to China two weeks later on April 22, 2020.  When the Chinese medical team arrived at Yangon Airport on April 8, 2020, they donated 5.3 tons of medical equipment to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports which included: 8,500 N95 masks, 60,000 medical masks, 5,500 sets of PPE, and a testing lab (see Project ID#90263). Moreover, the Chinese medical team also donated drugs worth RMB 4,337,334.25 to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports (see Project ID#93379).  Project ID#93378 captures the technical assistance. Project ID#90263 captures the 5.3 tons of donated medical equipment and testing lab. Project ID#93379 captures the drugs worth RMB 4.3 million.
combined_text:
# Sector
HEALTH

# Title
Chinese Government donates drugs worth RMB 4.34 million to Myanmar Ministry of Health in April 2020 (Linked to Project ID#90263, #93378)

# Description
On April 8, 2020, the Chinese Government officially sent 12 medical experts from Yunnan Province medical institutions to Myanmar to help fight the spread of COVID-19 (see Project ID#93378). During their stay, the team visited 43 medical institutions in Rangoon and Mandalay and held more than 50 exchange activities. For example, they visited Mandalay General Hospital's Department of Emergency Medicine to observe COVID-19 patients and discussed best practices for treating them. The team returned to China two weeks later on April 22, 2020.  When the Chinese medical team arrived at Yangon Airport on April 8, 2020, they donated 5.3 tons of medical equipment to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports which included: 8,500 N95 masks, 60,000 medical masks, 5,500 sets of PPE, and a testing lab (see Project ID#90263). Moreover, the Chinese medical team also donated drugs worth RMB 4,337,334.25 to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports (see Project ID#93379).  Project ID#93378 captures the technical assistance. Project ID#90263 captures the 5.3 tons of donated medical equipment and testing lab. Project ID#93379 captures the drugs worth RMB 4.3 million.
justification: Project involves donation of medical supplies and expertise, unrelated to energy or environmental impacts
evidence: Donation of drugs, medical equipment, and technical assistance for healthcare purposes

title: Chinese-Consulate General of Mandalay provide donation to 14 high schools in Amarapura Township, Myanmar (linked to #90341)
description: On September 2, 2020, the Chinese Embassy and Chinese-Consulate General of Mandalay provided a donation of an unspecified amount to 14 high schools in Amarapura Township, Mandalay Province in Myanmar. Consul General Chen Chen presented the donation. The purpose of this donation is to support the students' education.  The donation from the Chinese Embassy is captured via #90341, and the donation from the Chinese Consulate General is captured via #93389.
staff_comments: 1. The amount donated and the specific high schools donated too are not specified.2. Amarapura is a township of Mandalay city

title: Beiqi Foton contributes to a donation of a negative pressure ambulance in July 2020 to Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports (linked to #90396)
description: On July 16, 2020, a handover ceremony was held for the donation of a negative pressure ambulance from Beijing Automotive Group (BAIC) and Beiqi Foton to Myanmar's Ministry of Health and Sports. The ceremony was held at the Yangon Medical Research Center and was attended by embassy officials and government officials from Myanmar.  The donation was jointly provided by BAIC and Beiqi, BAIC's contribution was captured via #90396, and Beiqi's contribution is captured via #93495.
staff_comments: 1. The monetary value of the donated ambulance is unknown.

title: SPIC Yunnan International Company provides medical supplies worth RMB 1 million to Kachin Provincial Government to fight COVID-19
description: On April 8, 2020, State Power Investment Corporation (SPIC) Yunnan International Company officially donated medical supplies worth RMB 1 million to the Kachin Provincial Government in Myanmar. The donation included masks, protective clothing, disinfection tools, wash basins, rice, cooking oil, and other unspecified items. The monetary value of this donation is unknown.  On the same day, China General Technology Group (see Project ID #93538), ICBC (see Project ID #90265), Myanmar Wanbao Mining Copper Limited (see Project ID #93533), Myanmar Yangzi Mining Copper Limited (see Project ID #93536), and Shenzhen Industrial Park Group (see Project ID #93537) also provided separate, individual COVID-related donations to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports as well as the Myanmar Railway Bureau and Kachin Provincial Government. The donations included masks, protective clothing, infrared thermometers, and other anti-epidemic materials.
staff_comments: 1. SPIC and its subsidiaries made multiple donations to Myanmar in April 2020. They were on different dates and consisted of different goods. For a donation of toilets on April 20, see Project ID #90563. For a donation of medical equipment to hospitals on April 10, see Project ID #90270. For a donation of medical supplies to the Government of Myanmar on April 8, see Project ID #93532.
combined_text:
# Sector

# Description
On April 8, 2020, State Power Investment Corporation (SPIC) Yunnan International Company officially donated medical supplies worth RMB 1 million to the Kachin Provincial Government in Myanmar. The donation included masks, protective clothing, disinfection tools, wash basins, rice, cooking oil, and other unspecified items. The monetary value of this donation is unknown.  On the same day, China General Technology Group (see Project ID #93538), ICBC (see Project ID #90265), Myanmar Wanbao Mining Copper Limited (see Project ID #93533), Myanmar Yangzi Mining Copper Limited (see Project ID #93536), and Shenzhen Industrial Park Group (see Project ID #93537) also provided separate, individual COVID-related donations to the Myanmar Ministry of Health and Sports as well as the Myanmar Railway Bureau and Kachin Provincial Government. The donations included masks, protective clothing, infrared thermometers, and other anti-epidemic materials.
justification: Project is focused on healthcare support and COVID-19 relief, with no direct environmental or energy transition implications
evidence: Medical supplies donation including masks, protective clothing, and disinfection tools for COVID-19 response
